race.comment: RUBBLE 'N' FUDD (1) just found one better last start this track/distance racing on the speed. Fitter again and can build on his 50% win record. GEMS EAGLE (5) has not appeared since he got the cash over 1390m at Hobart on February 7. Seeks the hat-trick and has trialled well for the return. Has weight relief at this level and Darmanin's engagement is a decent push for his chances. SKY LAND (4) is progressing nicely and went close here last time over 1200m. Maps to advantage and can get into the finish. NGAPALI BEACH (6) found one better first-up and has more to give. Suited over the longer sprint and fitter will be hitting the line. Something for the Multiples: JOHNNIE PINCH (2)
